<dl id="n10030c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10030c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10030c"> 30(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> destination <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n10030c"> <li>FW isotext </li><li><ms href="#n10030c">MS BL 47482b-29</ms> </li><li>JJA 57:059 <a name="qA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/qda.htm#qA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/q/qa2d.htm#n10030c">Draft: III&sect;2A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Voulait-on envoyer un message confidentiel, on entourait la scytale d&apos;une bande &eacute;troite de parchemin, on &eacute;crivait dessus en langage convenu, en travers l&apos;h&eacute;lico&iuml;de form&eacute; par la bande, puis on la d&eacute;roulait et il ne restait plus qu&apos;&agrave; la faire parvenir <mark>au destinataire</mark> qui seul, pouvait d&eacute;chiffrer les signes cryptographiques &eacute;pars, en enroulant la missive sur la scytale dont il &eacute;tait d&eacute;tenteur. <font color="green">[If one wanted to send a secret message, a narrow band of parchment would be wrapped around the scytale. One would write on it, in a stipulated language, across the spiral formed by the band; then it would be unwound and subsequently all that would need to be done would be to send it to its recipient, who alone could decipher the scattered cryptographic signs, by winding the missive around the scytale in his keeping.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 23</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n10028e" href="n10all.htm#n10028e">N10 (VI.B.16):028(e)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
